{"aar_log_filter":{"content_index":0,"dropped_prefix_bytes":1866,"field":"text","message":"earlier repeated message_update events dropped","replaced_fields":2,"response_id":"gen-1781911499-dvCIQfmW8DvnfbvnCsbn","tail_bytes":0},"assistantMessageEvent":{"content":"Now I have a comprehensive understanding of the evidence. Based on my analysis of the record, I'm ready to submit my vote. The evidence shows:\n\n1. **Iran-initiated action**: The NOTAM A1010/26 was issued by Iran's Civil Aviation Authority/Civil Aviation Organization\n2. **Timing**: Effective from May 22 through May 25, covering the May 24 deadline\n3. **Non-weather cause**: The closure was security/military-related, not weather-related\n4. **Scope**: The NOTAM closed \"all airports in the west part of Tehran FIR\" with limited exceptions for daylight operations requiring fresh CAA approval\n5. **Corroboration**: Multiple independent sources (Indian Express, Abdi Media, Notamify) confirm the same NOTAM details\n\nThe key question is whether this constitutes a \"major closure\" under the rule. The rule defines a major closure as \"a broad closure, cancellation, or suspension of commercial flights transiting, arriving in, and departing from Iranian airspace or a major Iranian airspace region\" and explicitly states that \"limited exceptions to a broad closure will not disqualify such a closure.\"\n\nThe western Tehran FIR represents a major Iranian airspace region, and the closure of all airports in that region with suspension of all previous permissions and requirement for new CAA approval constitutes a broad suspension of commercial aviation operations. The limited daylight exceptions with fresh approval requirements are precisely the type of \"limited exceptions\" that the rule states do not disqualify a broad closure.\n\nWhile the evidence lacks official Iranian AIS/NOTAM database records, the preponderance standard does not require perfect custody when multiple independent sources consistently report the same specific details. The combined evidence makes it more likely than not that Iran initiated a qualifying major non-weather closure by the deadline.","contentIndex":0,"partial":{"api":"openai-completions","content":[{"text":"","type":"text"},{"arguments":{"args":"{\"vote\":\"demonstrated\",\"rationale\":\"The admitted record shows Iran's Civil Aviation Authority issued NOTAM A1010/26 closing all airports in western Tehran FIR from May 22-25 with limited daylight exceptions requiring fresh CAA approval. This constitutes a broad suspension of commercial aviation in a major Iranian airspace region, satisfying the rule's definition of a major non-weather closure by the deadline.\"}","tool":"aar_submit_council_vote"},"id":"call_dda7","name":"mcp","type":"toolCall"}],"model":"deepseek/deepseek-v3.1-terminus","provider":"openrouter","responseId":"gen-1781911499-dvCIQfmW8DvnfbvnCsbn","role":"assistant","stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1781911498851,"usage":{"cacheRead":38464,"cacheWrite":0,"cost":{"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"input":0,"output":0,"total":0},"input":499,"output":477,"totalTokens":39440}},"type":"text_end"},"message":{"api":"openai-completions","content":[{"text":"","type":"text"},{"arguments":{"args":"{\"vote\":\"demonstrated\",\"rationale\":\"The admitted record shows Iran's Civil Aviation Authority issued NOTAM A1010/26 closing all airports in western Tehran FIR from May 22-25 with limited daylight exceptions requiring fresh CAA approval. This constitutes a broad suspension of commercial aviation in a major Iranian airspace region, satisfying the rule's definition of a major non-weather closure by the deadline.\"}","tool":"aar_submit_council_vote"},"id":"call_dda7","name":"mcp","type":"toolCall"}],"model":"deepseek/deepseek-v3.1-terminus","provider":"openrouter","responseId":"gen-1781911499-dvCIQfmW8DvnfbvnCsbn","role":"assistant","stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1781911498851,"usage":{"cacheRead":38464,"cacheWrite":0,"cost":{"cacheRead":0,"cacheWri