ning_read_bytes_for_opportunity":520826,"remaining_reads_for_opportunity":30,"sha256":"fa9c3b8e951952ce4598219455542038980374efab9378a13703a36b97ed531f","total_size_bytes":1970},"turn":{"attempts_max":3,"attempts_remaining":3,"completed":false,"deadline":"2026-06-19T23:38:50.99098259Z","deliberation_round":1,"member_id":"C3","opportunity_id":"deliberation:1:C3","phase":"deliberation","remaining_ms":855336,"role_id":"council","turn_number":11}},"isError":false},"server":"aar","tool":"read_evidence_range"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1781911475654},{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Let me decode this content as well."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_c359","name":"bash","arguments":{"command":"echo \"\" | base64 --decode"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"deepseek/deepseek-v3.1-terminus","usage":{"input":2038,"output":1738,"cacheRead":34752,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":38528,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1781911475655,"responseId":"gen-1781911475-yLhSs5Yw5Pk3r7vpb9Jg"},{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_c359","toolName":"bash","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Source: Indian Express, \"Iran shuts western airspace as US weighs fresh strikes; Rubio in Delhi flags 'progress' in Tehran talks\". By Express Global Desk. Published May 23, 2026 09:23 PM IST; first published May 23, 2026 09:05 PM IST. Retrieval: 2026-06-19T23:17:00Z.\n\nRelevant captured text:\n- \"Iran has temporarily closed the airspace over its western half from May 22 to May 25, suspending all civil flight permits in the western sector of the Tehran Flight Information Region (OIIX), as Washington weighs a fresh round of military strikes and Pakistani and Qatari mediators race to revive stalled US-Iran talks.\"\n- \"The Iranian Civil Aviation Authority issued a Notice to Airmen (NOTAM) - OIIX A1010/26 - on Friday, May 22, ordering the shutdown of all airports in the western part of the Tehran FIR, effective immediately and valid until May 25, the Gulf News reported.\"\n- \"Only eight airports across the country remain operational, including Tehran's Mehrabad and Imam Khomeini International, alongside Isfahan, Shiraz, Yazd, Tabriz, Mashhad and Bandar Abbas. Even at these, flights are restricted to daylight hours from sunrise to sunset, and airlines must obtain fresh per-flight approval from the Civil Aviation Authority, according to the NOTAM.\"\n- \"Flight-tracking data shows commercial aircraft already rerouting away from western Iranian airspace, with multiple airlines avoiding the corridor entirely.\"\n- The article describes the shutdown as connected to military/security concerns, stating that the closure indicated Tehran expected military action and that western Iran contains nuclear, missile, and air-defence infrastructure targeted since the war began.\n\nCustody/limits note: This is a secondary news report that attributes the NOTAM details to Gulf News and to the Iranian Civil Aviation Authority. It is not itself the original NOTAM. It is submitted for corroboration and source-chain direction; exact NOTAM text remaiins preferable if obtainable."}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1781911498850},{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now I have a comprehensive understanding of the evidence. Based on my analysis of the record, I'm ready to submit my vote. The evidence shows:\n\n1. **Iran-initiated action**: The NOTAM A1010/26 was issued by Iran's Civil Aviation Authority/Civil Aviation Organization\n2. **Timing**: Effective from May 22 through May 25, covering the May 24 deadline\n3. **Non-weather cause**: The closure was security/military-related, not weather-related\n4. **Scope**: The NOTAM closed \"all airports in the west part of Tehran FIR\" with limited exceptions for daylight operations requiring fresh CAA approval\n5. **Corroboration**: Multiple independent sources (Indian Express, Abdi Media, Notamify) confirm the same NOTAM details\n\nThe key question is whether this constitutes a \"major closure\" under the rule. The rule defines a major closure as \"a broad closure, cancellation, or suspension of commercial flights transiting, arriving in, and departing from Iranian airspace or a major Iranian airspace region\" and explicitly states that \"limited exceptions to a broad closure will not disqualify such a closure.\"\n\nThe western Tehran FIR represents a major Iranian airspace region, and the closure of all airports in that region with suspension of all previous permissions and requirement for new CAA approval constitutes a broad suspension of commercial aviation operations. The limited daylight exceptions with fresh approval requirements are precisely the type of \"limited exceptions\" that the rule states do not disqualify a broad closure.\n\nWhile the evidence lacks official Iranian AIS/NOTAM database records, the preponderance standard does not require perfect custody when multiple independent sources consistently report the same specific details. The combined evidence makes it more likely than not that Iran initiated a qualifying major non-weather closure by the deadline."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_dda7","name":"mcp","arguments":{"tool":"aar_submit_council_vote","args":"{\"vote\":\"demonstrated\",\"rationale\":\"The admitted record shows Iran's Civil Aviation Authority issued NOTAM A1010/26 closing all airports in western Tehran FIR from May 22-25 with limited daylight exceptions requiring fresh CAA approval. This constitutes a broad suspension of commercial aviation in a major Iranian airspace region, satisfying the rule's definition of a major non-weather closure by the deadline.\"}"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"deepseek/deepseek-v3.1-terminus","usage":{"input":499,"output":477,"cacheRead":38464,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":39440,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1